Yes, pretty good summary, I'd wouldn't do nearly so well at any US sport.  The phrase "The fielding side may place its players pretty much anywhere they choose." made me smile as it brings to mind that there are certain rules about where fielders can be placed.  These rules came about because of the Bodyline series where (in part) the placement of fielders caused a diplomatic incident between England and Australia.
