Not a bad description! The main thing I'd add, for people coming to it for the World Cup specifically, is that the rule changes to make a shorter game (from 5 days down to 1) also impose pretty heavy restrictions on exactly where fielders can stand (although you're correct that it's "pretty much anywhere" in the 5-day version of the game). 
For example: a maximum number of people can field "outside the circle" (the circle...Read moreNot a bad description! The main thing I’d add, for people coming to it for the World Cup specifically, is that the rule changes to make a shorter game (from 5 days down to 1) also impose pretty heavy restrictions on exactly where fielders can stand (although you’re correct that it’s “pretty much anywhere” in the 5-day version of the game). 
For example: a maximum number of people can field “outside the circle” (the circle being the inner area within 30 yards of the pitch), and this maximum changes at various points in the game, and there are also rules that you have to have at least 3 people fielding on either side of the batsman. These rules are there to favour the batting team, encouraging them to play more exciting shots.
